-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-13/alstom-wins-288-million-sale-to-build-three-brazil-wind-farms.html
Alstom SA (ALO) , the worldâ€™s third-largest
power-equipment maker, will build and service three wind farms
in northeast Brazil for Brasventos SA.  The 200 million-euro ($288 million) contract is its biggest
sale of wind equipment in Brazil, Levallois-Perret, France-based
Alstom said today in a statement today. It will produce the
turbines at its factory in Bahia state.  Brasventos is a joint venture created by J. Malucelli
Energia and two units of  Centrais Eletricas Brasileiras SA. (ELET6)  The
three projects will be in Rio Grande do Norte and will produce
enough power for more than 100,000 homes.  To contact the reporter on this story:
